| Segment | Core Component | Functional Responsibility |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Edge Device** | `Acquisition` | Captures high-fidelity industrial telemetry directly from physical hardware interfaces[cite: 2]. |
| **Secure Gateway** | `Ingestion & Sanitization` | Handles edge connections, parses raw events, and executes cryptographic validation checks. |
| **Verification Layer** | `Cryptography & Trust` | Generates deterministic, verifiable proofs of state and weight values[cite: 2]. |
| **Evidence Registry** | `Immutability` | Operates as a distributed ledger to guarantee long-term, tamper-evident auditability[cite: 2]. |

## Core Design Principles

| Principle | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| 🔒 **Hardware-Assisted Trust** | Establishes hardware-rooted trust as the foundation for secure acquisition of physical events. |
| 📡 **Verifiable Telemetry** | Produces cryptographically verifiable telemetry that can be independently validated across organizational boundaries. |
| ⚡ **Cryptographic Integrity** | Protects telemetry throughout its lifecycle using modern cryptographic primitives, ensuring authenticity and integrity. |
| 🛡️ **Tamper-Evident Evidence** | Creates immutable, tamper-evident records that preserve the integrity and auditability of captured events. |
| 🚂 **End-to-End Traceability** | Maintains a verifiable chain of evidence from physical acquisition through digital verification and long-term audit. |
| 🔌 **Modular & Vendor-Neutral** | Designed with interoperable components to integrate with heterogeneous industrial environments while avoiding vendor lock-in. |

